http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Minister-opens-procurement-centres/article13991124.ece

District in-charge Minister Vinay Kulkarni inaugurated procurement centres for paddy and white jowar under the minimum support price scheme at the Agriculture Produce Market Committee (APMC) yard here on Saturday.Mr. Kulkarni said the fair average quality (FAQ) paddy would be purchased at the procurement centre at Rs. 1,510 per quintal and the process of purchasing had already begun.The procurement of white jowar would commence from January 16, he said.Mr. Kulkarni said that the government would purchase the grains under ‘Anna Bhagya’ scheme.He assured the farmers and traders that the road from new APMC yard to Savadatti road would be constructed at a cost of Rs. 3 crore.Procurement of white jowar to commence from January 16 atthese places